/F1 10 Tf
1 0 0 1 56 718.0 Tm (A stepped dust decline argues that the atmospheric reorganisation of deglaciation was) Tj
1 0 0 1 56 704.0 Tm (threshold-like rather than linear. Each step plausibly marks the crossing of a tipping point) Tj
1 0 0 1 56 690.0 Tm (in the position or strength of the southern westerly winds, which control how much dust) Tj
1 0 0 1 56 676.0 Tm (reaches Antarctica from the arid continents upwind.) Tj
1 0 0 1 56 662.0 Tm () Tj
1 0 0 1 56 648.0 Tm (The millennial plateau between the steps suggests the system could rest in an intermediate) Tj
1 0 0 1 56 634.0 Tm (state, neither fully glacial nor fully interglacial, for a long time before the second) Tj
1 0 0 1 56 620.0 Tm (threshold was crossed. This has consequences for how we model the pace of past and future) Tj
1 0 0 1 56 606.0 Tm (climate transitions, which too often assume smooth responses.) Tj
1 0 0 1 56 592.0 Tm () Tj
