1 0 0 1 56 560.0 Tm (High-resolution dust data from West Antarctica reveal that the last deglaciation's) Tj
1 0 0 1 56 546.0 Tm (atmospheric dust decline occurred in two abrupt steps bracketing a long pause. The finding) Tj
1 0 0 1 56 532.0 Tm (underlines that smooth-looking climate transitions in coarse records may hide discrete) Tj
1 0 0 1 56 518.0 Tm (jumps, and that resolution is not a luxury but a prerequisite for seeing how the climate) Tj
1 0 0 1 56 504.0 Tm (system actually moves.) Tj
